    "PushingPixels-v0": {
        "description": "Stub entry for PushingPixels-v0 (BlockPush with RGB observations, single target). The PushingPixelsSimulation builds a (3*frame_stack, H, W) tensor at every step and feeds it straight to the conv encoder — the conv encoder handles its OWN preprocessing (uint8→float, /255, bilinear resize to 180×240). The base-class ObservationNormalizer is constructed in __init__ but its `normalize(...)` method is never called in select_action. These dummy bounds exist solely to keep that __init__ from crashing.",
        "source": "Stub — never used at runtime; the conv encoder handles image preprocessing internally.",
